# AetherHUD

A Final Fantasy XIV overlay system built with Qt WebEngine, designed to provide seamless integration with the game's aesthetic and functionality.

## Features

- Click-through overlay windows that match FFXIV's UI style
- Per-job layout saving and restoration
- Hotkey support for visibility and window locking
- FFXIV-styled error pages and loading indicators
- Transparent background support
- Low-impact performance design

## Requirements

- Qt 6.x (or Qt 5.15+)
- CMake 3.16+
- C++17 compatible compiler
- WebEngine support

## Building

### Linux
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make
```

### Windows with MSVC
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake -G "Visual Studio 17 2022" ..
cmake --build . --config Release
```

### macOS
```bash
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
make
```

## Usage

### Basic Usage
```bash
./aetherhud [URL]
```

### Default Hotkeys
- **Ctrl+Shift+H**: Toggle overlay visibility
- **Ctrl+Shift+L**: Toggle window lock

## Development

### Project Structure
```
aetherhud/
├── src/
│   └── main.cpp
├── include/
│   └── version.h
├── resources/
│   ├── styles/
│   ├── images/
│   └── fonts/
├── CMakeLists.txt
└── README.md
```

### Building Documentation
Documentation can be built using Doxygen:
```bash
doxygen Doxyfile
```

